    {
      "id": 79854,
      "post_number": 14,
      "username": "InkuizitoriMoth",
      "name": "..... ......",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/peshkupauje.com/inkuizitorimoth/{size}/7035_2.png",
      "created_at": "2018-11-26T00:28:28.810Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Prei se eshte edhe element primordiali tjeter, eshte edhe distopia e luftes per ajrin qe eshte bere qe ne vitin 1929:</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox wikipedia\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Air_Seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">en.wikipedia.org</a>\n  </header>\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:200/313;\"><img src=\"https://peshkupauje.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3feb1705c8698d31c65068a7448111a5302f905b.jpeg\" class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Air_Seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">The Air Seller</a></h3>\n\n<p>The Air Seller (rus. Продавец воздуха) is a science fiction spy novel by Russian writer Alexander Belayev. It was first published in 1929, in several issues of Vokrug Sveta magazine.\n Meteorologist Georgiy Klimenko and his Yakut guide Nikola are investigating a strange wind anomaly in Yakutia, Eastern Siberia, when they are caught prisoner by a megalomaniac villain Bayley. With a gigantic air-sucking device, built by Swedish scientist Engelbrecht, Bayley is slowly stealing the Earth's atmosphere....</p>\n\n  </article>\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
      "reply_to_post_number": 13,
      "like_count": 0
